Numbers lifted at Naracoorte today as agents yarded 997 head of liveweight and open auction cattle. These sold to the regular buying field with the trade, feeders and restockers all active over the pens. Quality was mixed from good prime lots down to store types with a wide range on offer in a sale that was mostly dearer this week. 
   Yearling cattle with weight and condition were in short supply with the trade active from mostly 254c to 390c over both sexes with some feeder interest from 365c to 388c/kg, again over both sexes.
   Grown steers and bullocks saw trade support from 365c to 390c with feeder activity from 382c to again 390c/kg. Grown heifers to trade buyers sold from 330c to 368c with feeders operating here from 330c to 361c/kg. 
   Heavy cows sold from 322c to 335c with medium weights selling from 288c to 315c as lighter lots made from 250c to 280c/kg. Bulls which were of heavy weights sold from 300c to 360c as lighter lots made from 260c to 324c/kg. 
   Market reporter Peter Kerr 
Please note this report has been compiled remotely with limited data
